My feature directorial debut, a project I’ve been working on for 10 years in some form, has wrapped. ME, MY MOM & SHARMILA was a short, a play & now it’s in post production & inshallah we’ll share her with the world in 2023! Shot in 2 countries with 2 diff teams & 2 preps for 3 time periods, I just got back to LA after being gone for 5 months making this film. So many stories to tell & so much to share & catch up on. It’s the most fulfilling & life-changing thing I’ve ever done. I met & worked with incredible humans along the way. This post is all about Karachi, Pakistan. 

Thank u 2 my cast @amritkaur who is as heart-centered as she is talented. Just wait till u c her work. To @nimrabucha who’s range is as unparalleled as her laughter. To @hmzlhq who grounded us each day in ways he may not even know. And to the great @guleranaofficial you r a powerhouse. The stars in this film shine bright including @aliakazmi @meherjaffri @bakhtawar_mazhar @fawadkhan1984 @azramohyeddin @anwaarsheikh @danishirshadali @zahrakhan57 @sheemakermani & more!

My epic Pakistani producers @kamilchima & @caroln92 BROUGHT IT. My canadian producers @marcakamark @jpl @andriawilsonmirza r iconic. 

This film was blessed by the eye & extraordinary talent of DP @irwincine & genius production designer @mgpierson. 

My AD team was BEYOND: @farjadakhtar (my #1 in all the ways!) @bushraxjabeen & @saadkhatri51.

🙏🏾 incredible gaffer Asif Hassan & the whole grips team. There’d b no focus w/o the sharpest 1st AC in Karachi @waqasyounus85. Thx @studio146rentals 4 the gear & @iam_islam_ud_din for the tech cranes! 

Art team u brought this world 2 life @cyruskaranjia & @imrannaem with the help of Fawad Bhai and his set team. 

Wardrobe u know u my fav @fizzaejaz96 @faizruh @farihaahmed04 & the whole team!

Hair & Makeup love u 4 all your sexy lewks led by the fearless @minamilist & @nansongill & @mjhassan786 who cared 4 me when I had a 102 fever.

Sound was essential thx 2 the diligence of @fezedi & Faraz! And thanks to @a.hamza.98 & The Spot Boys - a band of boys I relied on each day. Choreo by @zarmeenayusuf___ = 🔥 & dialect coaching by @iamsunilshanker = 🤎 👊🏾

Stay tuned.

THAT’S A WRAP ON MY FEATURE: NOVA SCOTIA, CANADA EDITION! Entering post on my directorial feature debut ME, MY MOM & SHARMILA and reminiscing to our 14 day shoot in Nova Scotia, a place I lived for 11 years as a kid, and what a ride. We had the most experienced bad ass crew in Halifax. 

I couldn’t have been here without my ride or die producers @jpl @marcakamark & @andriawilsonmirza & line producer @kerrbrittany.

In it to win it with my brilliant cinematographer @irwincine.

Starring @nimrabucha @hmzlhq Ayana Manji @_aliakazmi and @amritkaur 

AD team was 🔥- thank you to my 1st for everything Jason Shipley — 2nd @melanigwood — 3rd @lifeofburgers — & 4th Wanda Arab — and to my Assistant @falymeva 🤎🤎🤎

No way we coulda got this right without our Scripty, the iconic Maggie Thomas.

And could not have gotten these beautiful pictures without our Grip & Lighting Team: Key Grip Marc Bourgeois & Dolly Grip Doug Betts and Gaffer @snipshots.

Wardrobe served it up - I 🤎🤎 you Costume Designer @modur_style Asst Costume Designer @thebossstitch & @busy_spider @bethley.boo 

Serving face for 12 days was Head of Makeup @charlgavaris & @kyla_creates — Hair got big and beautiful by @ailsagrace & Ashley Wells.

Thank you Paul Simmonds and Christian White on Locations in Halifax and @stevewaddenphoto in Sydney. 

Sound was stunning thanks to @oliviavking & Frank Kavanagh. And thx to badass stunts by @asaucypan & Randy Boliver.

SUNDANCE POST 1 — here’s a few moments from our glorious trip to @sundanceorg this year. I met my identity twin the incredible @tanfrance — we are both queer muslim Pakistani and love our greys. I got to dance to the beats of icon @djrekha and hug them after many many months. Hung with the incredible South Asian women in film I’m in a WhatsApp group with. Listen to amazing speakers including my wife @andriawilsonmirza & @latashagillespie at @amazonstudios. I hit the slopes and skied in Park City. YES IT WAS $$$!! Hung with the incredible @reframe_project team and all the directors and cinematographers in the ReFrame Rise cohort. Listened to academic and actress @saraseyed speak about Iranian women at the Sunrise Collective House and spoke on a panel with @nisha.ganatra & @nikdodani at the historic 1st ever South Asian Lodge brought to you by @define1497 and @shrutirya & @tanyaauthor. 

#sundance #film #parkcity #filmmakers

Sundance Drop 2. At the South Asian Lodge and the Gay Outpost and celebrating our friends’ films! Saw some incredible award-winning feature films including MUTT written & directed by @vuklk starring @lio.mehiel and produced by my manager @alexstegmaier and THE PERSIAN VERSION written & directed by friend & mentor @marakeshfilm and THE STROLL by @zackarydrucker — Went to @outfest’s Outpost and ran into so many beauties I adore. And celebrated some of my favorite short films of the year made by @daniabdeir Warsha and @jenrainin Holding Moses. So proud of @elegancebratton for all the accomplishments in the last 6 months and can’t wait to see more. And of course celebrated the guy who’s shown the world the possibility of Pakistani filmmakers @saim.sadiq with his game changing film @joylandmovie produced by @apoorvagc 

📸: @happymonday 
🧥 : @koel_shop 
🏠: @define1497 @tanyaauthor @shrutirya 🔥🤎
🎥: @sundanceorg 

#film #sundance #filmmakers #sundance2023

Telling stories centering queer Muslims is on brand for me. And I’m thrilled to facilitate the work and films of other creators. So excited to share that a feature doc that @andriawilsonmirza @babydaalproductions and I executive produced COMING AROUND — will world premiere at the incredible THESSALONIKI FILM FESTIVAL in Greece @filmfestivalgr
.
Repost from incredible first time feature director @sandraitainen — @comingarounddoc will have its world premiere at Thessaloniki next month in the Newcomers Competition✨

I couldn’t be happier and more proud of the whole team. @eabdelhadi and Fatten, thank you for letting me capture, reimagine and tell your story ❤️ It’s been an honor, and I know the film will make a difference in the world. I want to thank my day one partner, @chelsibullard for being on this journey with me. You always had faith in the project and put in work and your talent (even when nobody would give us money, lol). Thank you @uwaiduozee for all the creative vision and hard work you put into this. Thank you @13thgenfilm for joining the team when we needed you the most - your brutal feedback but also unwavering support. Thank you @thefawz and @andriawilsonmirza for also joining the team at a point when we needed your insight, and encouragement to film more and reopen the edit. @rababhajyahya I don’t know what I would’ve done without your guidance in the edit all this time. @sadiewh1te for your detailed attention in crafting the film’s musical world. @eccentric_orbit I’ve learned basically everything I know about filmmaking from you. David, @markbeckernyc , @lamyaisangry and @sabinekrayenbuhl thank you for giving some of the most crucial feedback. I also wanna thank everyone who watched rough cuts or supported our crowdfunding campaign - we couldn’t have done this without you. 

And last but not least, thanks to my family, especially my parents, for always breathing down my neck asking when this thing will be done: ”Eikö pitäisi olla valmista jo?”😅

Work hard, love the process, love the process all over again - and again. Catch us at Thessaloniki on March 7th and 8th <3 #tidf25 @filmfestivalgr @comingarounddoc

I thank all that is Divine for you. Shukria. You are Source. You are my Bollywood fantasy come true. @andriawilsonmirza

Happy Ramadan. This was my mother’s. She had it made when she lived in Libya in the 70s. As I continue to fight for Muslim and Queer out space, and as I work on my feature that honors mothers, it felt right.

Thank you to @glaad for having us - thx @anderfinn & Nick Adams and thank you for all the work you do to protect, fight for and uplift us. Now is a time for us to stand together with our community. We must be loud. And we must step up. And in the words of @glaad CEO & President @sarahkateellis “There is no LGBTQ without the T.” 

Congrats to all the nominees and winners including @chasejoynt & @samanthacurley and @911lonestar (@the_brianmichael I saw you!) and to @elegancebratton and @puertoricaninja and so many more!

Inna lillahi wa inna ilayhi raji'un. We belong to Allah and to him we return. This is the first night I met Karim Ladak, this sweet man. A man who became my brother immediately. A man who wasn’t blood but became my family. A man whose smile and heart were as bright and big as the sun. A man whose grace was only surpassed by his love for the arts and non profits and giving back to community. And traveling. He loved traveling and had a story from all over the world. This night we met we went to three restaurants and ordered everything. We both had shawls and we were so thrilled to finally be in family. He was only 1 of 2 witnesses at my Muslim wedding to @andriawilsonmirza. He wanted to throw us the big wedding reception we never had. He invested in my first real short film as a director with no questions asked. Because he believed in me. He was unlike anyone else. I will miss you brother. I know you are on that next journey and you’ve packed everything you need. Inshallah may your soul rest in peace.

For three weeks in March/April I shadowed Bradley Buecker the incredible director/producing director/executive producer of @911lonestar as a part of @ryanmurphyproductions ‘s @half.initiative — it was an incredible experience and i learned so many tips & tricks & insights that I’ve added to my directing tool belt. 

Repost from @half.initiative
•
“I loved the practical work we did together - he [Brad Buecker] invited me into his process, asked how I would block the scenes and we’d talk and walk through them and problem solve together.” -
Fawzia Mirza, Half mentee

Fawzia is a queer South Asian Muslim writer/director who is in post on her directorial feature debut, The Queen of My Dreams, shot in Canada and Pakistan.

Welcome to the Half family, Fawzia!

“Directing is about quick decision making under pressure, but shadowing Brad also reminded me of the importance of patience in finding the scene. Things moved quickly, and yet he was also always listening to everything and everyone around him. Watching him work and how he handled the set was a  representation of the kind of director I am striving to be.” @thefawz 

@ryanmurphyproductions #halfinitiative #mentorship #education #southasian #director #pakistan #canada #queer #femaledirector

Om Shanti. From God we come and to God we return. May his memory be a blessing. 

My dear friend Jitendra Bhatia died on Friday night in Dubai. He was 44. He was a brother. There was no one in the world like him. He was an incredible boss friend father and husband. He was generous and kind and funny and loving and had exquisite taste. We are all in a state of shock and disbelief. His loss is a reminder to love hard and love well. That we only have the time we have. And to take nothing and no one for granted. 

These pics are from his trip to LA a month and a half ago and when we saw him in Dubai right after we shot #TheQueenofMyDreams on our way home from Pakistan — he was going to come to London to see the film at its international premiere. He was so proud. Rest in peace brother and hopefully we meet in another life.

“In order to understand oneself, we really have to look not just at who we are, but at who our mothers are & who our ancestors are & who our elders are. This film has its roots in my first short film, which came out over 12 years ago & was also titled The Queen of My Dreams. That film was a very public conversation about a very private struggle of mine, which was me questioning ‘could I be queer & Muslim & love Bollywood romance & fantasy all at the same time?’ The answer that I came to was of course ‘yes’, & I embraced all those identities. Then I went on to make a one-person show about that & now there’s this feature film. Through creating art I’ve found healing & I believe that art does save lives. I’ve also found a great deal of compassion for my mother & for my motherland” @thefawz speaks exclusively with The Queer Review’s @jameskleinmann about her debut feature, The Queen of My Dreams, which world premiered @tiff_net & plays @britishfilminstitute London Film Festival this weekend. @raquel_willis on #liberation — Resonates. REPOST

So so so many people are silent right now. I know you’re fearful for whatever reason. That scarcity mindset has you in a chokehold, huh?

Liberation isn’t just about the grand things, the big structural changes, the massive cultural shifts, that new world that seems so far off in the distance.

Liberation starts within.

It starts with loosening those shackles and muzzles that still plague you.
It starts with bearing witness to suffering that isn’t yours.
It starts with realizing all of our destinies are bound.

When Azra, a queer Muslim grad student, hears of her father’s sudden death, she flies back to her ancestral home in Karachi, Pakistan for the funeral, where she is received by her conservative mother, Mariam, perpetually disappointed by Azra’s choices. As a self-assured Azra wrestles with Karachi’s customs and norms, we time travel back to Mariam’s own life in the city 30 years ago, a remarkably different era in Pakistan’s political and cultural history.

Join us for Reel Asian’s Opening Night screening of Fawzia Mirza’s feature debut, THE QUEEN OF MY DREAMS in Toronto. Starring Amrit Kaur, Nimra Bucha, Hamza Haq, Ayana Manji, and Gul-e-Rana, THE QUEEN OF MY DREAMS illuminates the deep and complex bond between generations of women who live in starkly different times yet negotiate their freedoms in strikingly similar ways.

Join us afterwards for our post-film reception - a perfect way to wrap up opening night festivities. Tickets on sale now!

We are proud to follow in the long tradition of protests for social justice and human rights at the Statue of Liberty, led by Indigenous, Black, and anti-war movements that came before us. Both US and Israeli politicians are telling us that the answer to all this bloodshed is more war. But the events of the past month have made it clear: The lives of Palestinians and Israelis are intertwined, & safety can only come from equality, justice, freedom for all.

We know that the bombs will only stop once there is sufficient mass outcry. It’s on us to build that outcry as fast as we possibly can. Ceasefire now to save lives!

Proud of you @salma.hindy for stepping up and speaking out against racism and being an incredible bystander. 

My values are centered in humanity. Which means I don’t think everything is funny. And I think some “jokes” are harmful and can incite violence and are deeply dangerous. And jokes that further oppress already oppressed communities are not funny. And that is how I center my writing as well. I learned these values doing sexual violence prevention work with @catharsisproductions for 9 years in Chicago. That work changed my life and made me a better person, and a better writer and director.

Proud to have been here.

🎥 💥 IN HOLLYWOOD: Hundreds of LA Jews & allies shut down Hollywood Blvd in the rain to demand an end to the Israeli government and military’s genocide of Palestinians. We’re staging an emergency sit-in at the beginning of rush hour and won’t leave until Biden and Congress say CEASEFIRE NOW.

We’re interrupting business as usual. The lives of 2.2 million Palestinians and 240 Israeli hostages in Gaza are in peril. The Israeli and US governments are endangering them in our names, using US-made bombs and billions of our tax dollars.

The lives and fates of Palestinians and Jewish Israelis are intertwined, and we’re fighting for the safety that can only come when everyone is free.

We’re here in Hollywood, a site of historic labor organizing and, at its best, storytelling that speaks truth to power. As LA Jews, we seek to build on this legacy — of which Jewish creatives have often been part, and for which many have historically been blacklisted and censored. But today, we refuse to be silenced, and we say, never again for anyone.

We are joined by entertainment industry workers of all stripes — including @lanzybear, @zoelisterjones, @mustafathepoet, @doitlikedua, @jamilawoods, @marawilson, @bejohnce, and @sandyhonig. We are joined by activists from local movements who connect their struggles in LA to those of Palestinians, including @LAtenants and @blmlosangeles.

The film and media industries play a role in perpetuating — and could play a role in ending — genocide and war. Today, we invoke our collective imagination to envision a just future of freedom and safety for all, beginning with ceasefire and hostage exchange now.
